View settings in paraview.

1) import film.iseg

2) to add color scale to visualize dislocation belonging to different slip systems (this step is needed only the first time you use paraview)

   Edit color map --> Color Scale --> Choose Preset --> Import
   Import both out/slipsys.xml and out/junctions.xml

3) Choose slipsys.xml or junctions.xml if you want to visualize dislocations belonging to different slip systems or junctions rispectively

4) Set the scale range from 1 to 20.

5) Check "use discrete color" and set the value to 20.



###########

-slipsys.xml ---> the color scheme matches exactly slip system order in BVD.* files

-junctions.xml ---> !!!Valid only for FCC materials!!!
               --->  14) edge Lomer-Cotrell lock
               --->  15) 60 degree Lomer-Cotrell lock
               --->  16) edge glissile
               --->  17) 60 degree glissile
               --->  18) Hirth lock
               --->  19) Collinear junction
               --->  20) GD segments